Hi Rhys, Dom,

Nice work! I appreciate the amount of work that goes into this sort of data analysis, especially when the data is in an awkward format, so well done for sorting through it all and doing some interesting analysis.

In terms of next steps, there are a couple of things would be useful. Firstly, given your time is limited, it would be helpful if you could write up what you've done in a brief report, with the emphasis on reproducibility - i.e. someone could easily reproduce the analysis based on your description.

If you have time for any more analysis, it would be interesting to focus a bit more on the sachet water use. Perhaps you could simplify the water sources into sachet water/not sachet water, and then construct a binomial regression model to assess the predictive power of the various independent variables.

Another thing you could do is expand the list of independent variables you're considering, using other parts of the census.

Mike may want to add/clarify some of these points.

Thanks for your hard work - this is really helpful to the project.

Cheers,
Simon

